Comment: It's the same concept with a layup.\'a0\'a0 Easier to go off the backboard.\'a0\'a0 You have a wider angle and you can also give it a lighter touch so if it bounces off the rim it's still going to drop in.\'a0 Utilizing the backboard effectively in basketball shooting techniques can significantly enhance a player's scoring ability. The insights provided by Allain, McDowell, and Barry shed light on the nuanced advantages of employing the backboard for various shots, including free throws and layups. Below is a refined exploration of these tips, offering a more detailed understanding of how to leverage the backboard to improve shooting efficiency.\
